@idanpa You could try my PR #156 or try adding git credentials from a terminal.
If you run the following nodejs script, it should either log your credentials or prompt to enter them. The issue I had was `execSync` getting hung by the prompt, because it was trying to ask for input and the extension wasn't noticing, so it just sat there waiting on a response and by using the synchronous `exec` function, the process could do nothing else until it finished waiting. If that is the problem you are having, then you should be fine once your git credentials store has credentials for github.
```node
const { execSync } = require('child_process')
const input = 'protocol=https\nhost=github.com\n\n'
const response = execSync("git credential fill", { input, encoding: "utf8" });
console.log(response)
```
If the script logged your credentials, then your problem may be different than the one I had. If you get the prompt, which may be a popup or in the terminal depending on the AskPass configuration, then you should be fine once the credentials have been entered.

