@lgarron Thank you for the merge!

> Note that this is not actually possible: https://www.w3.org/TR/clipboard-apis/#navigator-interface

I realize that the specification considers `navigator.clipboard` to be `readonly`, though if it's falsy, chances are the browser hasn't implemented it, and it's very likely just `undefined`.

Overwriting `navigator.clipboard` in such browsers is useful to avoid extra logic on call sites where your code assumes the presence of `navigator.clipboard`. So, the intention was not to unconditionally overwrite the native binding, but rather to set it in the first place in case it's missing.

Basically, while this is most definitely not possible due to the specification:

```js
navigator.clipboard = await import("clipboard-polyfill");
```

this should work as expected for older browsers:

```js
if (!navigator.clipboard) {
	navigator.clipboard = await import("clipboard-polyfill");
}
```

This should be fixed in the latest pre-release already: https://github.com/lgarron/clipboard-polyfill/releases/tag/v3.0.0-pre5

